comments.name: RT103R
comments.text: K103R is a polymorphic mutation that alone has no effect on NNRTI susceptibility. However, in combination with V179D, it reduces NVP and EFV susceptibility about 15-fold.

comments.name: RT118I
comments.text: V118I is a polymorphic accessory NRTI-resistance mutation that often occurs in combination with multiple TAMs.

comments.name: RT238R
comments.text: K238R is a common polymorphism that does not reduce NNRTI susceptibility.
